<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="work-v">work <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /wɜːk/    美 /wɜːrk/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 工作；(使) 劳动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>worked</strong> tirelessly <strong>for</strong> the charity throughout his life. 
他毕生为慈善事业孜孜不倦地工作。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>worked herself</strong> too hard. 
她工作起来太努力了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her husband worked two jobs to cover the bills.
她丈夫做两份工作来支付账单。</p><footer>2012 山东</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>从事职业：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Why do you choose to work in an international travel agency?
你为什么选择在一家国际旅行社工作呢？</p><footer>2012 福建</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I once <strong>worked as</strong> a reporter for my school broadcasting station.
我曾经在校广播电台当过记者。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(使) 运行；(使) 运转：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My mobile phone worked well yesterday, but I simply couldn’t turn it on this morning.
我的手机昨天用着还好好的，但今早就无法开机了。</p><footer>2012 陕西改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Do you know how to work the coffee machine? 
你知道怎么操作这台咖啡机吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>起作用；有效；行得通：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It takes sunscreen about fifteen minutes to start working.
防晒霜大约在（涂抹）15分钟后开始起作用。</p><footer>2019全国改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The medicine works more effectively if you drink some hot water after taking it. 
你吃完这种药后再喝点热水，药效会更好。</p><footer>2009 浙江</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We won’t know how the plan works till we have tried it out. 
直到我们尝试后才能知道这个计划是否行得通。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>努力取得：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Jennifer received great support from her family as she worked to earn her degree.
詹妮弗在努力获得学位的过程中得到了家人的大力支持。</p><footer>2020山东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="work-on">work on</h3>
<p>1.<strong>从事于；致力于：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After Jack had sent some e-mails,he started working on his project.
杰克发了几封电子邮件后，就开始做他这个项目的工作。</p><footer>2012山东</footer></div>

<h3 id="work-out">work out</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>算出 (calculate)；总共达：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m just trying to work out how much I spend each month. 
我正在尽力算出我每月的开销。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The travelling expenses <strong>work out at</strong> 12 dollars per day each. 
每人每天的旅行费用总共12美元。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>解决 (solve)；把...弄清楚：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To work out the difficult maths problem, I have consulted Professor Russell several times.
为了解出这道数学难题，我已经请教拉塞尔教授好几次了。</p><footer>2014 陕西</footer></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>制定 (出)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Trained exercise teachers can help you work out a training plan and keep you active. 
训练有素的体育老师能帮你制定一套训练计划，使你保持活力。</p></div>

<p>4.★ <strong>产生结果；被证明有效</strong><br />
to develop or progress, especially in a good way：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everything worked out OK in the end. 
事情的结果还不错。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I want to follow David’s example but it never worked out for me.
我想效仿大卫的做法，但这对我没有效果。</p></div>

<p>5.★ <strong>锻炼；训练：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I go to the sports club and work out once a week. 
我一周去一次体育馆锻炼。</p></div>

<h3 id="work-through">work through</h3>
<p>1.<strong>解决（问题）；调整（情绪）：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>How did Ms Yi Jiefang work through her sadness after her son's death?
易解放女士在儿子死后是如何调整悲伤情绪的？</p><footer>北师大新必修③-8</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I had as much fun sailing the seas as I now do <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (work) with students.  （2016 浙江改）  </li>
<li>Marty <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (work) really hard on his book and he thinks he’ll have finished it by Friday.  （2015 陕西改）<br />
A.worked<br />
B.has been working<br />
C.had worked<br />
D.has worked  </li>
<li>You can’t predict everything. Often things don’t work <strong><em>_</em></strong>_as you expect.  （2011 江西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. working  2. B  3. out  </p></div>